"Freehold Going Concern hotel with potential trading upside for incoming
owner operator"

CBRE Hotels is delighted to offer this hotel opportunity located in Katoomba, New South Wales.

* Simple operation and considerable potential trading upside for new owner
* Freehold Going Concern (Land and Business)
* 1,917 square metre site
* 39 guest rooms
* Facilities include restaurant, theatre, bar, guest lounge, pool and parking
* 1.5 hours from Sydney
* Great Western Highway upgrade set to reduce travel time
* Revenue in excess of $640,000 for FY2011-12

For Sale by Expressions of Interest closing at 4:00pm on Wednesday 12th June 2013, unless sold prior.

•4 separate cinemas + ample onsite car parking
•Potential to add value through active management & additional tenancies
•Excellent main road exposure and close to station and amenities
•Alternate uses including but not limited to Religious, Entertainment, Tourism or Conference Centre (STCA)

Under Instructions from Stephen Hathway & Joe Atkinson as Voluntary Administrators

In conjunction with May Estates
Gregory May
